@node "STAR_TREK_THE_MOTION_PICTURE" "ST-THE MOTION PICTURE  "

                      @{b}@{i}Star Trek - The Motion Picture@{ub}@{ui}

  The crew of the USS Enterprise reunite once again after 10 years
 from the cancellation of the original series to save Earth from a
 destructive power that swallow ships and destroy planets.  The 
 Enterprise must find a way to stop before it collides with Earth.


 @{fg shine}Starring:@{fg text}      William Shatner
                Leonard Nimoy 
                DeForest Kelley

 @{fg shine}Also Starring:@{fg text} James Doohan
                Walter Koenig
                George Takei
                Nichelle Nichols

 @{fg shine}Co-Starring:@{fg text}   Stephen Collins as "Captain Decker" 
                Persis Khambatta as "Lt.  Illa"

 @{fg shine}Teleplay:@{fg text}      Harold Livingston and Alan Dean Foster  

 @{fg shine}Screenplay:@{fg text}    Harold Livingston  

 @{fg shine}Directed by:@{fg text}   Robert Wise
@endnode

@node "THE_WRATH_OF_KAHN" "THE WRATH OF KAHN  "

                     @{b}@{i}STAR TREK II:  The Wrath of Khan@{ub}@{ui}
                                   1982
 
  The second STAR TREK movie opens with a new generation of Starfleet
 cadets being trained by Lt.  Saavik, a brilliant young cadet of Vulcan
 descent who hopes to pass the Kobayashi Maru simulation excerise, an
 important part of Academy training and serve aboard a Federation starship.
 Now an Admiral, James T.  Kirk, is unhappy with his current ground
 assignment and broods over memories of times past while his friends Spock
 and Dr.  McCoy urge him to look ahead toward a new command.
 
  The USS Reliant, under the command of Captain Clark Terrell and
 First Officer Pavel Chekov, is on a survey mission in the Ceti Alpha system
 in search of a suitable planet on which to test a device known as Genesis,
 an invention designed to be able to transform lifeless planets into
 fruitful, life-sustaining environments.
 
  Beaming down, they are surprised to discover Kirk's old nemesis
 Khan Noonian Singh, a genetically engineered super-soldier from the late
 20th Century and his followers, whom Kirk had exiled 15 years earlier.  His
 world has since been laid to waste by severe gravitational shifts caused by
 the destruction of a neighboring planet and many of his people, including
 his wife.  Khan has vowed revenge against Kirk and, after taking over the
 wills of Terrell and Chekov through the use of mind-controlling Ceti Eels,
 Khan and his people hijack the Reliant and set off in search of Kirk.
 
  Aboard the Enterprise, Kirk receives a garbled message from Dr.
 Carol Marcus, chief scientist of the project and an old flame, complaining
 of interference by Starfleet with her work.  Sensing that she and her
 project are threatened, Kirk takes command and changes course toward Regula
 One, where Genesis is based.
 
  While en route, Kirk encounters Khan, who unleashes a surprise
 barrage of phaser fire, nearly destroying the Enterprise.  By tapping into
 Reliant's security access code, Kirk is able to lower Khan's shields and
 damages his ship in turn.
 
  Enterprise reaches Regula One to find the station ravaged, the
 material of Genesis gone and Terrell and Chekov left behind.  Finding the
 transporter set for an area deep within a nearby asteroid.  Kirk, McCoy and
 Saavik beam down only to be ambushed by David Marcus who believes Kirk to
 be responsible for the attack on the space station.  Kirk recognizes David
 to be his son, but before he can explain the truth, Terrell and Chekov,
 still under the influence of the Ceti Eels placed by Khan draw their
 phasers on Kirk and his party.  Unable to bring himself to kill Kirk,
 Terrell turns his phaser on himself instead.  Chekov's Eel is destroyed,
 leaving him unconscious, but intact.
 
  Khan, enraged that his latest bid to kill Kirk has failed,
 transports away the Genesis Torpedo and leaves the landing party behind.
 While Kirk and his team await rescue from the Enterprise, he is awed by the
 remarkable results of the Genesis experiments.  He also explains to Lt.
 Saavik how he managed to beat the Kobayashi Maru no-win scenario by
 reprogramming the test.
 
  Finally transported to the Enterprise, Kirk challenges Khan to the
 final battle within the Mutara Nebula, inside of which neither sensors nor
 deflector shields would operate, thus making the starships evenly matched.
 After a cat and mouse game, Khan is finally defeated, but, in a last act of
 vengeance, activates the Genesis Torpedo.
 
  Spock realizes that in order for the Enterprise to escape, he must
 get the main warp engines back on line, whatever the cost, so he enters the
 highly radioactive reaction chamber to restore the ship's warp drive.
 Spock's efforts succeed, and the Enterprise warps out of range of the
 Genesis explosion, but Kirk's jubilance is short-lived when he discovers
 their escape has cost the life of his closest friend and First Officer.
 After jettisoning Spock's coffin into space orbit of the newly formed
 Genesis planet the Enterprise returns home.
 
 
 
 @{fg shine}Starring:@{fg text}            William Shatner
                      Leonard Nimoy
                      DeForest Kelley
 
 @{fg shine}Co-Starring:@{fg text}         James Doohan
                      Walter Koenig
                      George Takei
