@endnode

@node "THE_SEARCH_FOR_SPOCK" "  "

                   @{b}@{i}STAR TREK III:  The Search For Spock@{ub}@{ui}
                                   1984

  The third picture in the STAR TREK movie series begins where the
 second film left off.  Grieving over the loss of Spock, the Enterprise crew
 returns home to Earth where they find that the Enterprise is to be
 decommissioned to make way for more state-of- the art space vessels.  Kirk
 later receives a visit from Spock's father, Sarek, who believes Kirk to be
 in posession of Spock's Katra, or living essence, and tells him that it
 must be returned with Spock's body, to Vulcan. 
 
  They later discover that Dr.  McCoy is in fact the keeper of the
 Katra.  McCoy must thus be taken to Genesis to recover Spock's body and
 bring it to its final resting place on Mount Seleya where his body and soul
 be re-fused into one complete entity. 
 
  Regardless of the cost, Kirk must put Spock's future before his
 career and with the help of his crew, Kirk steals the Enterprise from
 spacedock and escapes at warp speed to Genesis to complete his mission.
  
  
 
 @{fg shine}Starring: @{fg text}     William Shatner 
                DeForest Kelley
 
 @{fg shine}Co-Starring: @{fg text}  James Doohan
                George Takei
                Walter Koenig
                Nichelle Nichols
                Merritt Butrick 
                Christopher Lloyd
 
 @{fg shine}Written and Produced by:@{fg text}  Harve Bennett
@{fg shine} Directed by:@{fg text}   Leonard Nimoy
@endnode

@node "THE_VOYAGE_HOME" "THE VOYAGE HOME  "

                      @{b}@{i}Star Trek IV:  The Voyage Home@{ub}@{ui}
                                   1986

  The crew of the USS Enterprise tried in absentia, face both Federation
 and Klingon charges.  On Vulcan, they agree to return home for sentencing.
 Over Earth, an alien probe wreaks havoc in attempt to speak to an
 intelligent life form:  whales.  The crew must journey back in time to
 retrieve the extinct creatures.
 
